{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 26,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 26 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:1",
      "text": "As dew in harvest, and as rain in summer, so honour is not seemly for a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:2",
      "text": "As birds and sparrows fly, so a curse shall not come upon any one without a cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:3",
      "text": "As a whip for a horse, and a goad for an ass, so is a rod for a simple nation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:4",
      "text": "Answer not a fool according to his folly, lest thou become like him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:5",
      "text": "Yet answer a fool according to his folly, lest he seem wise in his own conceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:6",
      "text": "He that sends a message by a foolish messenger procures for himself a reproach from his own ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:7",
      "text": "As well take away the motion of the legs, as transgression from the mouth of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:8",
      "text": "He that binds up a stone in a sling, is like one that gives glory to a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:9",
      "text": "Thorns grow in the hand of a drunkard, and servitude in the hand of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:10",
      "text": "All the flesh of fools endures much hardship; for their fury is brought to nought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:11",
      "text": "As when a dog goes to his own vomit, and becomes abominable, so is fool who returns in his wickedness to his own sin. There is a shame that brings sin: and there is a shame that is glory and grace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:12",
      "text": "I have seen a man who seemed to himself to be wise; but a fool had more hope than he.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:13",
      "text": "A sluggard when sent on a journey says, There is a lion in the ways, and there are murderers in the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:14",
      "text": "As a door turns on the hinge, so does a sluggard on his bed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:15",
      "text": "A sluggard having hid his hand in his bosom, will not be able to bring it up to his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:16",
      "text": "A sluggard seems to himself wiser than one who most satisfactorily brings back a message.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:17",
      "text": "As he that lays hold of a dog’s tail, so is he that makes himself the champion of another’s cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:18",
      "text": "As those who need correction put forth fair words to men, and he that first falls in with the proposal will be overthrown;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:19",
      "text": "so are all that lay wait for their own friends, and when they are discovered, say, I did it in jest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:20",
      "text": "With much wood fire increases; but where there is not a double-minded man, strife ceases.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:21",
      "text": "A hearth for coals, and wood for fire; and railing man for the tumult of strife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:22",
      "text": "The words of cunning knaves are soft; but they smite even to the inmost parts of the bowels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:23",
      "text": "Silver dishonestly given is to be considered as a potsherd: smooth lips cover a grievous heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:24",
      "text": "A weeping enemy promises all things with his lips, but in his heart he contrives deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:25",
      "text": "Though thine enemy intreat thee with a loud voice, consent not: for there are seven abominations in his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:26",
      "text": "He that hides enmity frames deceit: but being easily discerned, exposes his own sins in the public assemblies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:27",
      "text": "He that digs a pit for his neighbour shall fall into it: and he that rolls a stone, rolls it upon himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.26.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:28",
      "text": "A lying tongue hates the truth; and an unguarded mouth causes tumults.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
